In many KBs, temporal annotations are also used for positive statements. A typical statement, in Wikidata, for instance, qualifies that Albert Einstein's German citizenship ended in 1933, or that he received the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921.\footnote{\url{https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q937}} Annotating completeness and recall statements with temporal qualifications appears therefore quite natural.